## ðŸ”‘ Fields & Definitions

### 1. ID
- **Definition**: Unique identifier for each policyholder.  
- **Type**: Numeric/Text (Primary Key).  
- **Business Use**: Maintains data integrity, links claims and renewals.

### 2. Birthdate
- **Definition**: Policyholderâ€™s date of birth.  
- **Type**: Date.  
- **Business Use**: Used to calculate **Age**, segment into groups (<25, 25â€“40, 40â€“60, 60+).

### 3. Car Color
- **Definition**: Carâ€™s exterior color.  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Pattern analysis (fraud detection, theft trends).

### 4. Car Make
- **Definition**: Brand/manufacturer (Toyota, BMW, Ford).  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Claims analysis by brand â†’ risk & repair cost.

### 5. Car Model
- **Definition**: Specific model (Corolla, X5, etc.).  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Luxury vs economy claim trends.

### 6. Car Use
- **Definition**: Purpose (Personal, Commercial, Commute).  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Risk profiling (commercial cars = higher risk).

### 7. Car Year
- **Definition**: Year of manufacture.  
- **Type**: Numeric.  
- **Business Use**: Car age = Current Year â€“ Car Year; risk segmentation.

### 8. Coverage Zone
- **Definition**: Geographic risk area (Urban, Rural, Zone Aâ€¦).  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Regional claims/risk analysis.

### 9. Education
- **Definition**: Highest education attained.  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Marketing, claim behavior insights.

### 10. Gender
- **Definition**: Policyholder gender.  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Risk & demographic breakdowns.

### 11. Marital Status
- **Definition**: Single, Married, Divorced, etc.  
- **Type**: Text.  
- **Business Use**: Compare claims by marital stability.

### 12. Parent
- **Definition**: Whether the policyholder has children (Yes/No).  
- **Type**: Boolean.  
- **Business Use**: Segment household profiles.

### 13. Claim Amt
- **Definition**: Total claim amount.  
- **Type**: Numeric (Currency).  
- **Business Use**: KPI for losses, fraud detection.

### 14. Claim Freq
- **Definition**: Number of claims filed.  
- **Type**: Integer.  
- **Business Use**: High-frequency claimants = higher risk.

### 15. Household Income
- **Definition**: Annual household income.  
- **Type**: Numeric.  
- **Business Use**: Segmentation by income band; premium targeting.

### 16. Kids Driving
- **Definition**: Number of kids licensed to drive.  
- **Type**: Integer.  
- **Business Use**: Family risk estimation, accident probability.

